FTSE 100 scales new peaks on rate hopes , profits . UK ' s FTSE 100 index of leading shares hit a new milestone on Wednesday as solid corporate results and a weaker pound drew buyers back into stocks , even as the Bank of England contemplated an interest rate hike . The key share price index added 65 . 6 points to close at 5 , 026 . 2 , passing the 5 , 000 level for the first time ever . Advancers beat decliners by a margin of two - to - one . Dealers and strategists said expectations the BoE would raise rates at the end of its two - day meeting tomorrow had diminished . 
